The paper deals with algorithms for finding the $k$-sink on dynamic path networks, which involves graph theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which suggests the category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The algorithms presented in the paper involve sorting and searching, which are common techniques in cs.AL (Algorithms). The paper also involves network optimization, which suggests the category cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves computational complexity analysis, which suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
